org.jikesrvm.compilers.opt.bc2ir

Class OperandStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jikesrvm.compilers.opt.bc2ir.OperandStack

  • final class OperandStack
extends Object
    Simulates the Java stack for abstract interpretation in BC2IR.

    This class is intended to be used by a single thread. Methods from this class do not provide any error handling.

    The total amount of Operands that can be accepted by an operand stack is called the capacity of the operand stack. It is determined when the stack is created. The capacity is distinct from the current number of operands on the stack which is called the size of the operand stack.
